
## 1. What HTML is and why we use it

**HTML (HyperText Markup Language)** is the standard language used to create web pages.

We use HTML to:

* Structure content on a webpage
* Tell the browser **what things are** (headings, paragraphs, images, links, etc.)
* Build the basic skeleton of a website

HTML does **not** style pages (that‚Äôs CSS) or add behavior (that‚Äôs JavaScript). 
It‚Äôs all about **structure and meaning**.

---

## 2. What an HTML tag is

An **HTML tag** is a keyword wrapped in angle brackets (`< >`) that tells the browser what kind of content 
it‚Äôs dealing with.

Examples of tags:

```html
<p>
<h1>
<div>
<span>
```

Tags usually come in pairs:

* **Opening tag**: `<p>`
* **Closing tag**: `</p>`

---

## 3. Opening tag, closing tag, and content

Most HTML code looks like this:

```html
<p>Hello world</p>
```

* `<p>` ‚Üí opening tag
* `</p>` ‚Üí closing tag
* `Hello world` ‚Üí content

Together, they form a complete unit.

---

## 4. What an HTML element means

An **HTML element** is the **entire thing**:

* Opening tag
* Content
* Closing tag

### Example:

```html
<p>Hello world</p>
```

This whole line is **one HTML element**.

### ‚≠ê Key difference (important!)

* **Tag** = just `<p>` or `</p>`
* **Element** = `<p>Hello world</p>`

üëâ Think of it like:

* **Tag** = the container
* **Element** = the container + what‚Äôs inside

---

## 5. Self-closing (void) elements

Some HTML elements **do not have content**, so they don‚Äôt need a closing tag.
These are called **self-closing** or **void elements**.

Examples:

```html
<img src="image.jpg">
<br>
<hr>
<input>
```

They:

* Have only one tag
* Do not wrap content

---

## 6. Block-level vs inline elements

### Block-level elements

* Start on a new line
* Take up the full width of the page

Examples:

```html
<h1>This is a heading</h1>
<p>This is a paragraph</p>
<div>This is a div</div>
```

### Inline elements

* Stay in the same line
* Take only as much space as needed

Examples:

```html
<span>Inline text</span>
<a href="#">A link</a>
<strong>Bold text</strong>
```

---

## 7. Commonly used HTML tags (with simple examples)

### `<h1>` ‚Äì Heading

```html
<h1>Welcome</h1>
```

### `<p>` ‚Äì Paragraph

```html
<p>This is a paragraph.</p>
```

### `<div>` ‚Äì Block container (layout/grouping)

```html
<div>
  <p>Inside a div</p>
</div>
```

### `<span>` ‚Äì Inline container (small text styling)

```html
<p>This is a <span>word</span> in a sentence.</p>
```

---

## 8. Summary: Tag vs Element (very clear)

| Term        | Meaning             | Example        |
| ----------- | ------------------- | -------------- |
| **Tag**     | Markup inside `< >` | `<p>`          |
| **Element** | Tag(s) + content    | `<p>Hello</p>` |


